# Plan: Move test temp dirs from `.test-tmp/` to `os.tmpdir()`

## Problem
The previous fix (2806622a) moved test temp dirs from `$HOME` to a project-local `.test-tmp/` directory. While this stopped polluting `$HOME`, `.test-tmp/` is not the right location — we should use the OS-provided temp directory (`os.tmpdir()` → `/tmp` on Linux, `$TMPDIR` on macOS).

## Approach
Replace all `resolve(import.meta.dir, "../.test-tmp")` patterns with `os.tmpdir()` + a namespaced subdirectory (`sentry-cli-test/`). Export the constant from `test/helpers.ts` so all consumers share a single definition.

## Files to Change (in order)

### 1. `test/helpers.ts`
**Export `TEST_TMP_DIR` so other files can import it instead of computing it independently.**

```diff
+import { tmpdir } from "node:os";

-const TEST_TMP_DIR = resolve(import.meta.dir, "../.test-tmp");
-mkdirSync(TEST_TMP_DIR, { recursive: true });
+export const TEST_TMP_DIR = join(tmpdir(), "sentry-cli-test");
+mkdirSync(TEST_TMP_DIR, { recursive: true });
```

- Update JSDoc on `createTestConfigDir` (line 27): remove "project-local" wording, say "OS temp directory"

